<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-08-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-08-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="77" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-08-17"><hi rend="italic">August 17,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1370.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to confirm your telegram
                            of August 15.</p>
                        <p>I have made it perfectly clear to Prince Ch’ing that the date for signing
                            of the completed treaty, October 8, is absolute and not contingent on
                            any action of Russia.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">E. H. Conger.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>